wdi-AG.LND.FRST.K2.def: Forest area is land under natural or planted stands of trees of at least 5 meters in situ, whether productive or not, and excludes tree stands in agricultural production systems (for example, in fruit plantations and agroforestry systems) and trees in urban parks and gardens.
wdi-AG.LND.FRST.K2.name: Forest area
wdi-AG.LND.FRST.K2.source: Food and Agriculture Organization, electronic files and web site.
